# Product Operating System — gitignore strategy
#
# Everything that contains your real, private, company-specific content is
# ignored by default. The `_template/` folder ships parallel placeholder
# versions for sharing this OS as a template.
#
# To share the OS with someone else, push to a public/template repo with
# this .gitignore in place. Your private content stays local.

# === Private content (your real stuff) ===
# Company-specific context — never share by accident
company/about.md
company/okrs.md
company/kpis.md
company/teams.md
company/tools.md
company/procedures.md
company/glossary.md
company/stakeholders/*.md
!company/stakeholders/README.md

# Product-specific work
products/*/
!products/README.md
!products/.gitkeep

# Personal identity content — all of it stays private
identity/*.md
!identity/README.md
identity/examples/**
!identity/examples/README.md
!identity/examples/**/.gitkeep

# Drafts and works-in-progress
workspace/*
!workspace/README.md
!workspace/.gitkeep

# Cross-cutting learnings (often contain confidential context)
knowledge.md

# Auto-generated OS changelog (private, local only)
CHANGELOG.md

# Configuration with personal preferences
# (uncomment if you want config to stay private)
# config.md

# === Standard ignores ===
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Editor folders
.vscode/
.idea/

# OS files
desktop.ini
